Black demons are large demons that inhabit various locations across RuneScape. They use Magic attacks that can hit up to 672. They are stronger than their greater demon cousins and are often assigned by Sumona, Duradel/Lapalok, Kuradal, Morvran, Mandrith, and Laniakea as Slayer tasks. Black demons drop infernal ashes as a 100% drop and are considered a good source for crimson charms, with more than a 40% drop rate for these charms. Because of their high combat level and relative ease to defeat, black demons are often killed for their starved ancient effigy drops and Slayer experience.

Black demons originate on Infernus, where they were called Alyaroth, as do the other demons seen in Gielinor. They are part of the Avernic race, which were tribal and primitive, and slaves to whoever was ruling Infernus at the time. At the time of Palkeera's memory of the realm, they were enslaved by the cannibalistic Chthonians, who were unable to consume the Avernics for some reason. Among the Avernic demons, the Tsutsaroth were the dominant tribe, ruling over the Alyaroth and Byzroth in a brutal manner.

Taverley Dungeon[edit | edit source]

There is a large spawn of eleven black demons deep within the Taverley Dungeon. Fastest methods to get to them:

  • Dungeoneering cape teleport to Taverley hellhound resource dungeon, and run south to the large room of demons.
  • Taverley lodestone, run south to the dungeon entrance, skip over the metal drain (requires 80 Agility), or enter the pipe near the entrance (requires 70 Agility). The Agility requirements can be boosted, e.g. +5 from summer pies.
  • If the player does not have the Agility level required to use the shortcuts, a dusty key will be required to access the area. The key can be added to the steel key ring, which can be put on the tool belt.
  • Teleport option from five dragon trinkets to teleport to the blue dragons.

This spot can yield very good Slayer experience on tasks if using a dwarf multicannon. The best option for banking is using the Taverley Lodestone, and running south to the bank. The Taverley bank is within sight of the dungeon entrance, which can be right-clicked to enter from just outside the bank. Other options for fairly quick banking are to teleport to the Castle Wars bank chest and return using the balloon transport system or to Home Teleport to Falador lodestone and use the west Falador agility shortcut.

Brimhaven Dungeon[edit | edit source]

There is a small spawn of four black demons at the Brimhaven Dungeon, but one of these is isolated in a chamber with three bronze dragons. Fastest methods to get to them:

  • Dungeoneering cape teleport to Brimhaven metal dragon dungeon
  • Karamja lodestone is right outside the dungeon. 875 coins are required for every entry (fee is waived once the hard Karamja achievements are completed).

Getting in and out is no threat but can be time consuming. A cannon can be used to defeat these demons, but it can also fire at the nearby wild dogs and iron dragons.

Chaos Tunnels[edit | edit source]

A group of four black demons can be found in the main area of the Chaos Tunnels. Without regarding the possibility of misfires, the fastest route to the demons involves using the entrance at level 6 Wilderness (with the gargoyles). If misfires occur, expect travel time to be longer or shorter. A dwarf multicannon and its variants cannot be brought into the dungeon.

Chaos Tunnels resource dungeon[edit | edit source]

Nine black demons can be found in Chaos Tunnels resource dungeon, although one cannot be reached with melee. Level 70 Dungeoneering is required to access the resource dungeon, and, as with the main Chaos Tunnels, a dwarf multicannon and its variants cannot be brought in.

This can be accessed very quickly by using the Dungeoneering cape to teleport there directly.

Edgeville Dungeon[edit | edit source]

Edgeville Dungeon is considered a convenient place to slay in relative peace, as there are three spawns, enough to sustain one player. It is recommended to stick to the north side of the room to avoid being harassed by aggressive skeletons and poison spiders. There is also a ladder to the north that goes up to a safe zone with the Obelisk of Air. It is useful for whenever you need a reprieve to heal or use Home Teleport to the Edgeville lodestone for banking.

Dungeoneering cape's teleport to Edgeville Dungeon chaos druids dungeon is fairly close, otherwise you must go through the Edgeville Dungeon through the entrance south of Edgeville.

Wilderness Ruins[edit | edit source]

A group of sixteen black demons can be found in the ruins south of the Demonic Ruins (level 37 to 40 Wilderness). This is a highly dangerous and remote location, with the following travel options:

  • Annakarl Teleport to Demonic Ruins, and run south. This requires running through aggressive packs of Kal'gerion demons, greater demon berserkers, and greater demon ash lords.
  • Boss portal attuned to Dragonkin Laboratory and run southwest. This goes through much the same monsters as above, but at least the arrival point itself is not dangerous.
  • Wilderness sword teleport to the herb patch, and run a long way east. Goes through hellhounds and onyx dragons.

If the player is killing black demons for a Slayer assignment at this location, then they can gain 20% additional Slayer experience by equipping a demonic skull (however, this automatically opts in PvP). This stacks with Slayer contracts for +40% total.

The black demons here are stronger, boasting a higher combat level and health.

Strategy[edit | edit source]

Main article: /Strategies

Wear the best Ranged gear available to you. The higher the level of Ranged armour you wear, the better defence will be towards magical monsters such as demons.

Alternatively using Silverlight or its upgraded version, Darklight, will work as the black demon's weakness, allowing melee to be viable.

Black demons have a high defence against melee attacks, as they are magic-based monsters.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • Slayer Masters say that the black demon is the strongest demon. However, there are several demons which are stronger.
  • There was a graphics error with the transparency of the wings where, if you looked closely when the wings were lined up with the body of the demon, you could see right through the solid body of the demon through the wings. This has since been fixed.
  • Black demons received a graphical update on the 28th January 2013. The graphics were shown in an earlier video, as seen here. In the video, the combat level of the demon appears to be at least 300 but this did not show up in the update.
